<subSubSection id="0DE671A50B456B2F40F6D2A0FA29926C" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="DD9076708F8E4BB6D5E3E13EAB4F5F58" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6852261A8B4963210C7704056FD682AF" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Venezuela, Rio Manizanes, coll. Rumrich, 4.4.1990.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F2ECE39A0FE1437CFC6EB7AF3DC73AC" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Valves lanceolate, dorsiventral, dorsal and ventral margins convex; ends barely protracted, rounded, or subcapitate, slightly deflected to ventral margin; length 34.5-42.7 
<normalizedToken id="9529A55A533CE4EB50AB3ED83362E867" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, breadth 10.0-12.0 
<normalizedToken id="86B06DEFCB1E06E18EA88B00C5D2B2CE" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, L/B ratio 3.1-4.0; axial area linear, arched, central area indistinct to slightly rounded; striae 9-12 in 10 
<normalizedToken id="8E1B62706741841B9CA563C76A21A431" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, becoming 11-12 toward ends, 1 isolated pore; 21-24 punctae in 10 
<normalizedToken id="BE8E751A04B8969B7E52E1A135FA1EA9" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B14EC9CAB7696439DB3A60CBD4BEBE59" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C885C4521F1CA906DC928DC91DDC0B1A" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD5DACE5BC4F610BCB4B5A5F1B5E1F65" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<bibRefCitation id="3C8BC1197D174515AC927E38CD5B8F6F" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="7259AE49316674B141FDF2D6BFB46A84" authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis id="E40B4F3D6A82CD6A0B0B507C700555AE" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded differences in the size, length/breadth ratio, and the presence of only one stigma as consistent diagnostic differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="971AC5E9EC5495D9178D3B68053F92DB" authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis id="B6F6F30F8C2DB1D479AEFEE3C23CDDBF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="66F3E97DA488D6B0B8981F974DE0C9D7" author="Tuji, A" journalOrPublisher="Diatom" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="49 - 54" publicationUrl="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" refId="B22" refString="Tuji, A, 2007. Type examination and typification of Cymbella affinis Kuetz., C. turgidula Grunow and C. uenoi Skvortsov. Diatom 23: 49 - 54, https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" title="Type examination and typification of Cymbella affinis Kuetz., C. turgidula Grunow and C. uenoi Skvortsov." url="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" volume="23" year="2007">Tuji (2007)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the occurrence of specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="8412A6F8479A55F9A91EF14B457A39B8" authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis id="50E936DD472B7CF854A9B3FC05008AEA" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 1-3 isolated pores, which was also observed by 
<bibRefCitation id="0CA9E2B05B876DB4248298EF96BA1884" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
in his material. We observed a continuum between the metric characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="923F2530C5AEBCF16A3B1071118E96C3" authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis id="C7DE7E4CC580B3258A27D915E6F6CE10" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="502BB220E940AE40E826819F534DCB3E" authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis id="C8D9C2F6DED857D8E20B394320AC58B8" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, even in those characters that were considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="FA2CFA55424D045EE24FB40B016CB165" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
as differentiating. However, the outline was more lanceolate, the ends more protracted and slightly deflected to the ventral side, and the degree of dorsiventrality was lower in 
<taxonomicName id="86612B089353B7EE466F4E3CE5F7051D" authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis id="C539B7633BCD381E65842CA1D903670E" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to 
<taxonomicName id="0644F2A071A942AB88DB15A9EFF9D6BD" authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis id="2C69FE99A818DF19741A3A9F8DE889DF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
